chunk_content: • The infants reported as tested under the revised PMTCT_EID indicator are not necessarily the same infants whose positive results would be reported under the PMTCT_HEI positive infant disaggregate in the same quarter. • In MER, there is no way to report that an infant is linked in a quarter different from when the infant received the diagnosis. PMTCT_HEI_POS_ART is a disaggregate of PMTCT_HEI_POS, meaning that the ART status of an infant must be reported in the same quarter in which the infant is reported in HEI_POS. It is important for countries to track infant linkage and ensure that all infants are initiated on treatment as soon as possible, even if it cannot be reported in MER. How to collect: This indicator should be collected from the clinical source (i.e., HIV-exposed infant registers or patient records) to ensure unduplicated patient counting and patient care.
